    {
      "id": "f34d3ec9d65e79fc5ef473ee1ef1ff0180db10fb",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-05-30 10:23:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nFan Yong,\none defect is that this patch should remove the use of \"32bitapi\" in parallel-scale-nfs.sh so that it doesn't hide whether this change is fixing the real problem or just being skipped.\n\nYu Jian,\nis it possible for you to test that this patch fixes the NFS export problem, once 32bitapi is removed from parallel-scale-nfs.sh setting of cl_mnt_opt=\"$MOUNTOPT,32bitapi\"?\n\nIs there a Test-Parameters line that would run the NFS testing automatically?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "790d2b4aefffcc178c5d47a7602368cf4135462f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 131,
        "name": "Jian Yu",
        "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "yujian"
      },
      "date": "2013-05-30 15:03:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Yu Jian, is it possible for you to test that this patch fixes the NFS export problem, once 32bitapi is removed from parallel-scale-nfs.sh setting of cl_mnt_opt=\"$MOUNTOPT,32bitapi\"?\n\nFan Yong, could you please remove \"cl_mnt_opt\" from lustre/tests/parallel-scale-nfs.sh along with this patch?\n\n> Is there a Test-Parameters line that would run the NFS testing automatically?\n\nYes. Like this:\n\n Test-Parameters: envdefinitions=SLOW=yes \\\n testlist=parallel-scale-nfsv3,parallel-scale-nfsv4",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "ff0adf0e919e2b736bada8681a5e412fa1c24d68",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-05-31 00:21:00.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nOnly this patch (without 32bitapi)  cannot make master to work via NFS re-exporting, because we still need patch nfs-utils to support 64-bit ino#. But I do not know how to make nfs-utils patch to be tested by Maloo.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "4c72bfd1b7f04666436d4118bbe37569e04313be",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 131,
        "name": "Jian Yu",
        "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "yujian"
      },
      "date": "2013-05-31 02:54:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Only this patch (without 32bitapi) cannot make master to work via NFS re-exporting, because we still need patch nfs-utils to support 64-bit ino#. But I do not know how to make nfs-utils patch to be tested by Maloo.\n\nIf the nfs-utils patch is ready, I can help run the test manually.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "04d46c68725c44cc02ab5f9fb5436265393ed5bb",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-05-31 02:56:13.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThe patch for nfs-utils is already under LU-2904 as a attachment.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "c029e7110074d34cde95bf671b266402c7368ba9",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 131,
        "name": "Jian Yu",
        "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "yujian"
      },
      "date": "2013-06-06 03:07:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> The patch for nfs-utils is already under LU-2904 as a attachment.\n\nHere is the test result:\n\n NFS client: 2.1.6 RC1\n NFS server/Lustre client/Lustre server: http://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/15771\n Distro/Arch: RHEL6.4/x86_64 (with patched nfs-utils-1.2.3-36.el6.x86_64.rpm)\n\n parallel-scale-nfsv3 passed without \"32bitapi\" and \"fsid=0\":\n https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/468b73a0-cde0-11e2-96ef-52540035b04c\n\n parallel-scale-nfsv4 failed without \"32bitapi\" and \"fsid=0\":\n https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/fc211cea-cde2-11e2-96ef-52540035b04c",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "3e4763fe3faf8c692e8c70d3694128bed7412240",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 131,
        "name": "Jian Yu",
        "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "yujian"
      },
      "date": "2013-06-07 04:03:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Verified\n\nparallel-scale-nfsv4 passed without \"32bitapi\" but with \"fsid=0\":\n https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/e7c9b7d2-cf1f-11e2-9212-52540035b04c",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "e32f5dc6502e6afbaa9176a80b2172d29e0e1340",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-06-08 04:42:09.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nHi Andreas,\n\nBefore the nfs-utils patched, we cannot remove the mount options of \"32bitapi\". Yujian has verified that \"this patch + nfs-utils\"  works for the nfs tests.\n\nSo whether I need to refresh this or not? Thanks!",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "5f8544986960ccc04132f470dc7e68905dbe61e1",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-06-08 06:18:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nFan Yong, maybe I misunderstand, but does fsid=0 hide the fsid returned from the filesystem, or is this a special code for \"fsid=0 means get the fsid from the filesystem\"?\n\nI guess we'll just have to watch the upstream RHEL and SLES distros to ensure they get the 64-bit inode patch included. Could you please also send the patch to Jeff Mahoney @ SuSE so that he gets it into their next update?  The RHEL NFS maintainer was already included in the original email list.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "ea44c38f4b1792fee99ec8c50bab87bd36e4df5b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-06-08 06:42:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n> Fan Yong, maybe I misunderstand, but does fsid=0 hide the fsid returned from the filesystem, or is this a special code for \"fsid=0 means get the fsid from the filesystem\"?\n> I guess we'll just have to watch the upstream RHEL and SLES distros to ensure they get the 64-bit inode patch included. Could you please also send the patch to Jeff Mahoney @ SuSE so that he gets it into their next update? The RHEL NFS maintainer was already included in the original email list.\n\nThe \"fsid=0\" is required by NFSv4 only as explained in exports manual as following:\n\n\"For NFSv4, there is a distinguished filesystem which is the root of all exported filesystem.  This is specified with fsid=root or fsid=0 both of which mean exactly the same thing.\"\n\nSo it is not related with Lustre.\n\nI have forward the nfs-utils patch to Jeff. Let's wait his respond.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "794ac6b31aa18f518e1bc9fca25c77a0dfa5602c",
